Date: Tue, 28 Apr 2026 15:25:20 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 08/25] [switch] Externals/SFML: bump nested submodule for
 Switch OS arm

The vendored SFML at Externals/SFML/SFML is itself a git submodule.
This commit advances its pointer to a switch-build-prep branch that
patches include/SFML/Config.hpp:106 with a __SWITCH__ alias to
SFML_SYSTEM_LINUX. Without it, the OS-detection cascade #errors out
on devkitA64 because the toolchain defines neither _WIN32, __APPLE__,
nor __unix__.

Dolphin only uses SFML's Network module; libnx exposes BSD sockets
+ select() with the same shape as Linux glibc.
---
 Externals/SFML/SFML | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/Externals/SFML/SFML b/Externals/SFML/SFML
index 0fa201c969..f9b84ab137 160000
--- a/Externals/SFML/SFML
+++ b/Externals/SFML/SFML
@@ -1 +1 @@
-Subproject commit 0fa201c969e48ecc253581c5841ce73f44d42f49
